TECHNICAL REGULATIONS OF THE RUSSIAN CHAMPIONSHIP OF THE RUSSIAN FEDERATION FLAG FOOTBALL LEAGUE IN THE VENUE, ALL-RUSSIA COMPETITION IN THE VENUE
from 14.02.2021 20:40
February 15-17, 2021,
gymnastics hall of the CSKA sports club, Moscow, Leningradsky Prospekt, 39, building 1
Day of arrival February 14, 2021, day of departure February 18, 2021.
PARTICIPANT AGE, TEAM AND PERSONAL RESULTS, ADMISSION REQUIREMENTS
Competitions are individual with a team score, athletes from the teams of the subjects of the Russian Federation participate, in one age group — men, women.
Sports competitions among men, women (born in 1998) are attended by athletes of younger age groups if they have the necessary sports qualifications.
Athletes admitted to the competition only in the individual competition, do not participate in the distribution of points for the team competition.
The results are not reset for athletes who did not participate in these competitions, and team points are not awarded.
Team points are awarded in full to all teams whose athletes compete in accordance with the approved territorial affiliation.
Participating organizations are allowed to exceed the quota by adding two athletes to the team to participate in each type of relay race.
In the relay race, team members must compete in sports uniforms of a single color.
In case of violation of this provision, the team may not be allowed to participate in the competition.
In the relay race, athletes can only compete for the team of one territory.
The competition is open to athletes with a rank not lower than 1st sports rank.
The competition is open to athletes nominated by regional teams, who have passed a medical examination and received permission from a doctor.
Applications for the competition are accepted only through the unified information system of the All-Russian Federation of Athletics.
The deadline for submitting applications for competitions is February 12, 2021 at 18.00 Moscow time.
The Commission for Admission of Participants and for Confirmation of Applications Submitted in Advance and for Providing the Necessary Documents for the Application will work on February 14 from 10:00 to 16:00 hours at the CSKA Fitness Center, in the hall of the conference room, 3rd floor, at the address: Leningradsky Prospekt, 39, building 1.
All athletes, coaches and team representatives included in the application must complete anti-doping educational online courses on the official website of RUSADA before the start of the competition and obtain a certificate.
SPORTSMEN, TRAINERS, REPRESENTATIVES ARE REQUIRED TO PROVIDE IN THE SECRETARIAT A REPORT WITH A NEGATIVE RESULT OF THE PCR-TEST ON COVID-19, WITH THE DATE OF COLLECTION OF BIOMATERIAL NOT LATER THAN 72 HOURS FROM THE MOMENT OF APPEARANCE BEFORE THE MANDATORY COMMITTEE.
The territorial affiliation of athletes is determined in accordance with the Unified Information System and the decision of the Transfer Commission.
Official training on the competition arena on February 14 from 16:00 to 19:00. On competition days - outside the competition time.
Pre-competition warm-up is carried out on site, under the guidance of senior judges for the disciplines.
Collection and registration of participants will be carried out in the registration area (Sai Koot).
The Say Coote will be located after the second turn next to the core push sector.
When passing registration, the participant is obliged to show the judge the correspondingly fastened chest number.
The departure of participants from the place of registration to the competition venues in technical disciplines is carried out under the guidance of the senior judge/referee for the discipline, in running disciplines — under the guidance of the assistant starter.
It is forbidden for participants to leave the competition area without the permission of the referee.
Registration of participants in running events begins 40 minutes before the start of the event and ends 10 minutes before the start of the event.
Registration for technical events begins 50 minutes before the start of the event and ends 25 minutes before the start of the event.
Registration for pole vault starts 80 minutes before the start of the event and ends 55 minutes before the start of the event.
Participants who did not show up for registration will not be allowed to compete.
Participants are given trial attempts in accordance with the rules of the sport.
In the 60 m and 60 m hurdles races, competitions are held in 3 rounds, the entry to the next round will be determined at the end of the application period.
In the 200 m, 400 m, and 800 m races, competitions are held in 2 rounds, with qualification for the final based on time.
In the event of a tie in the running events to advance to the next round, the tie shall be resolved in the following manner: 1. The results shall be checked to the nearest 1/1000th of a second; 2. If, after the application of point 1, the tie persists, a draw shall be held.
In the 1500 m, 3000 m, 5000 m and 4x400 m races, finals are held.
In the jumping and throwing events, qualifying (in the case of more than 16 declared athletes) and final competitions are held, for which it is necessary to qualify.
If the number of participants who have met the standard is less than 12 people, then athletes are brought up to this number in accordance with the best qualification results.
If a participant, declared in several types of program, did not appear in one of the types without a valid reason, then he is not allowed to compete in the subsequent types.
Athletes are allowed to use personal equipment, provided that this equipment is approved by the Organizing Committee.
Personal ammunition (core) the athlete must submit for inspection to the equipment service (inventory room in the warm-up area) no later than 2 hours before the start of the event.
During the competition, it is not allowed to replace ammunition.
In case of equality of results in determining the winner in vertical jumps, a re-jump is carried out.
All protests and appeals shall be submitted in accordance with the Rules - Rule 8 (146).
An oral protest shall be made by the representative/competitor immediately after the result in question has been announced.
A written appeal must be submitted no later than 30 minutes after the official announcement of the result for this discipline.
Protests and appeals concerning an athlete's right to compete or their eligibility to belong to a particular team are submitted in a similar manner to the Appeals Panel.
The results of the team competition are determined in accordance with the Regulations. The results of all-Russian competitions are included in the team competition.
The winner and the runners-up of the competitions in running events are obliged to appear in the award department, located in the manege, no later than 10 minutes after the end of the event.
Winners of the championship are awarded championship medals, winners of all-Russian competitions (200 m and 5000 m)
Any athlete who does not start in the running or technical event is not allowed to participate in the subsequent events and is considered to have withdrawn from the competition.
If an athlete progresses to the next round after the preliminary round of the competition but then does not compete in that event, they will be disqualified from further competition, including the relay.
In the event that the athlete submits medical documents about the impossibility of participating in any kind of competition, he may be allowed to participate in other disciplines of the competition, but only on the following day, at the discretion of the technical delegate.
The doctor during the competition is located in the area provided by the organizers.
The GSK technical meeting with the official representatives of the teams will take place on February 14 at 18:00 in the conference hall of the CSKA VFC manege.
The meeting of GSK members with the competition judges will take place on February 14 at 18:40 in the conference hall of the CSKA VFC gym.
