Somnologist named the reasons for sleep problems
Otolaryngologist Sofia Cherkasova spoke about foods and habits that interfere with healthy sleep.
As the specialist noted, sleep problems often arise due to products containing caffeine.
We are talking primarily about tea, coffee, chocolate and any cocoa-containing desserts.
It is worth limiting their use before bedtime, since they not only interfere with falling asleep, but also make sleep "jumpy", which means they do not allow the body to fully recover.
According to the doctor, it is better to stop consuming caffeine-containing products 6-8 hours before bedtime.
Otherwise, they contribute to reducing the threshold of excitability of the nervous system and, as a result, there are difficulties with falling asleep.
Alcohol also negatively affects the ability to fall asleep.
The doctor clarifies that small doses of alcoholic beverages contribute to relaxation and do not affect sleep.
However, amounts exceeding 36 grams when converted to pure alcohol lead to various sleep disturbances, such as superficial sleep and frequent nocturnal awakenings.
In addition, in order to prevent problems with falling asleep, a somnologist recommends giving up spicy food and large portions.
Large volumes and spicy food contribute to an increase in internal body temperature, which negatively affects the ability to fall asleep.
For healthy sleep, it is not only necessary to comply with the external temperature regime: the optimal air temperature is 18-20 degrees - but also the absence of elevated body temperature.
According to Cherkasova, it is not worth abusing heavy food before bedtime, since it will not allow the body to fully recover and rest: it will be forced to spend energy on digestion.
The doctor also recalled that the absence of healthy sleep and accumulated sleep deprivation affect the quality of life and habitual activity, so it is extremely important to adhere to a sleep and rest schedule and to allow the body to recover.
