A tanker with a diesel engine from a previously Russian-flagged vessel was not allowed into the port of Spain
The Tarragona Maritime Command of the General Directorate of Merchant Fleet of the Ministry of Transport of Spain has prohibited the vessel Maersk Magellan from entering the city's port to unload diesel fuel, since the cargo comes from the Nobel vessel, which sailed under the Russian flag until July 1, 2022, the Spanish Ministry of Transport reported.
"The Maritime Command of the Tarragona Headquarters of the Trade Fleet of the Ministry of Transport, Mobility and Urban Development has prohibited the entry into the port of Tarragona for the unloading of diesel fuel on the vessel "Maersk Magellan" under the flag of Singapore, because the cargo it is carrying comes from the vessel under the Cameroonian flag "Nobel", which until July 1, 2022, sailed under the Russian flag," the ministry said in a statement.
The measure was adopted in accordance with the legislation of the European Union, which prohibits access for any vessel registered under the Russian flag from April 16, 2022, or that has changed its flag after February 24, 2022.
The ministry specified that the check was carried out on February 9, after which the ban was agreed.
The ministry recalled that this is not the first time that ships have been prohibited from entering Spanish ports.
In April 2022, the port of Barcelona denied access to the Maltese-flagged Black Star vessel, which was carrying cargo from a Russian-flagged vessel.
In 2022, after the strengthening of anti-Russian sanctions, the EU, USA and Great Britain introduced restrictions on the supply of Russian petroleum products, and then decided to limit fuel prices.
Since December 5, 2022, a price ceiling has been introduced on sea shipments of oil from the Russian Federation by hostile countries.
At that time, a ceiling was set for Russian oil at $60/barrel.
Also, since December 5, the EU embargo on sea shipments of oil from Russia has been in effect.
Problems with entry into Argentina for pregnant Russian women have been explained
According to the expert, against the backdrop of the influx of those wishing to give birth to a child in Argentina, the country's authorities have become more attentive to the entry of foreign citizens into their territory.
Difficulties with the entry of pregnant Russian women into Argentina are connected with the fact that the country's authorities are not interested in a mass influx of foreigners who want to obtain citizenship for their children and a residence permit for themselves and then leave.
This is reported by Lenta.ru with reference to SPbGU Professor Viktor Heifetz, editor-in-chief of the magazine "Latin America".
According to him, no country supports such a practice.
He noted that Argentina does not approve of turning the country into a transit point rather than a final destination.
This applies to those who violate constitutional practice.
As the expert explained, the child will retain Argentine citizenship, but the court will make a decision on granting an Argentine passport to the parents after obtaining a residence permit.
If it turns out that they did not actually live in Argentina and immediately left, they may be denied citizenship.
This applies not only to Russians, but also to citizens of other countries.
Recently, as the specialist pointed out, maternity tours to Argentina are especially popular among Russians and Ukrainians.
Recall that Argentina provides citizenship under the "right of soil", that is, if a person was born on its territory.
The Argentine passport opens up the possibility of visa-free travel to 170 countries, including EU states and the UK.
Earlier it was reported that Argentina began to withdraw residence permits for Russians who received the document through the birth of a child, but left the country.
Buenos Aires is interested in reducing such cases.
It was also reported that six pregnant Russian citizens were denied entry to Argentina on suspicion of providing false information about the purpose of their trip.
