Currently, all facilities that were under the management of "Zabota" have been excluded from the register of licenses for the management of multi-apartment buildings.
Their total area was 64.8 thousand square meters.
All houses are located in the regional center.
The fact that they were left without a management company is known to the administration of Kirov.
In accordance with the requirements of Russian legislation, the State Housing Inspectorate informed the mayor of the situation.
Recall that in January 2023, the governor of the Kirov region, Alexander Sokolov, set a task for employees of the State Housing Inspectorate to eliminate two-thirds of the region's management companies by spring, since there are too many of them.
The legality of the governor's demands raised doubts among the Kirov Communists.
They appealed to the regional prosecutor's office and asked to bring Sokolov to administrative responsibility.
Presumably, the same position could be taken by the Federal Antimonopoly Service.
Antimonopoly officials also allegedly asked the prosecutor's office to check the legality of the region's head's actions.
Wildberries will make parcel pickup points paid
The Wildberries marketplace will make packages at pickup points paid from February 13.
Their cost will vary from 6 to 15 rubles.
Now the packages are provided by the owners of the pick-up points.
In case of their absence, a fine is imposed.
Starting Monday, February 13, packages at Wildberries pickup points can no longer be picked up for free.
Marketplace users received a notification, according to which buyers who need the package will have to pay for it from 6 to 15 rubles.
This amount will be debited from the card specified in the personal account.
According to the company, this step will help to reduce the use of plastic and will contribute to the preservation of nature.
As follows from the appendix to the offer to provide services for the delivery of mail to individuals, the executor, that is, the person who opened the pickup point, must provide the packages free of charge at the request of the client.
At the same time, they must be designed in certain colors and have a specified image.
The packages are purchased at the expense of the owners of PVO, if this obligation is not fulfilled, a fine of 10,000 rubles is imposed on them for each violation.
Earlier, Wildberries customers accused the platform of debiting funds from cards, the data of which were previously deleted from the personal account.
As buyers fear, this is associated with great security risks.
The support service, in turn, explained that this is provided for in the user agreement.
As follows from it, the company has the right to debit money from remote cards without notifying the client if payment from other sources does not go through for one reason or another.
The company, commenting on the situation, stated that calculations with buyers are carried out with the permission of customers, and there can be no leakage of bank card data.
Photos from February 2023.
